    <a name="who-can-help"></a>
    <h2>Who can help?</h2>
    <h3><a class="external" href="http://www.esta.vic.gov.au/None/EmergencyVic+Landing+Page">Triple Zero (000) Emergency</a></h3>
    <p>Triple Zero (000) should be called when police, fire or ambulance attendance is needed in a life-threatening or time critical situation.</p>
    <p>Be prepared to describe your location as accurately as possible. Your mobile phone only shows call-takers your billing address, not your current GPS location.</p>
    <h3><a class="external" href="http://www.ses.vic.gov.au/warnings/emergency-contacts">132 500 – SES Emergency</a></h3>
    <p>Call from anywhere in Victoria for flood emergency response.</p>
    <h3><a class="external" href="https://www.emv.vic.gov.au/our-work/victorias-warning-system/emergency-broadcasters/">Emergency radio and TV stations</a></h3>
    <p>Tune to ABC Local Radio, commercial and community designated radio stations or Sky News TV.</p>
    <h3><a class="external" href="http://www.ses.vic.gov.au/warnings/emergency-contacts">1300 842 737 – SES Information Line</a></h3>
    <p>The SES Information Line only operates during major flood events.</p>
