    <h2>Warning Systems</h2>
    <p>The Victoria State Emergency Service and the Bureau of Meteorology work together to warn the community about flooding. Current flood warnings for Victoria can be found on the<br/>
    <a class="external" href="http://www.emergency.vic.gov.au/">Vic Emergency</a><br/>
    <a class="external" href="http://www.bom.gov.au/vic/warnings/">Bureau of Meteorology website</a></p>
    <p>Remember, you may not receive any official warning. Emergency assistance may not be immediately available so be aware of what is happening around you to stay safe. Never wait for a warning to act. Flooding can happen anywhere, at any time, and can be caused by more than just rain. Even if you don't live near a river or creek, flooding may still happen in your area. For more information about floods visit the SES <a class="external" href="http://www.ses.vic.gov.au/get-ready/floodsafe/">FloodSafe page</a></p>
