    <a name="flood-safety-messages"></a>
    <h2>Flood safety messages</h2>
    <p>What to do during minor flooding</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Decide what you and your family will do if flooding affects you</li>
        <li><a class="external" href="http://www.bom.gov.au/vic/flood/index.shtml">Monitor weather forecasts and stream levels</a></li>
        <li>Consider moving livestock to higher ground</li>
        <li>Take care when driving – do not drive through flood water</li>
        <li>Take care around rivers, stream and drains – do not enter flood water</li>
        <li>Be prepared to act if your situation changes</li>
        <li>If you require assistance from SES call 132 500</li>
    </ul>
    <p>What to do during moderate flooding</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Decide what you and your family will do if you become isolated or if you need to evacuate</li>
        <li>Consider moving livestock and machinery to higher ground – if safe to do so.</li>
        <li><a class="external" href="http://www.bom.gov.au/vic/flood/index.shtml">Monitor weather forecasts and stream levels</a></li>
        <li>Take care when driving – do not drive through flood water</li>
        <li>Take care around rivers, stream and drains – do not enter flood water</li>
        <li>If you require assistance from SES call 132 500</li>
    </ul>
    <p>What to do during major flooding</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Decide what you and your family will need if you become isolated or if you need to evacuate</li>
        <li>Take care when driving – do not drive through flood water</li>
        <li>Take care around rivers, stream and drains – do not enter flood water</li>
        <li>If you require assistance from SES call 132 500</li>
    </ul>
    <p>What to do if you need to evacuate</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Act Now – take immediate precautions to protect your life and property</li>
        <li>Raise belongings by placing them on tables, beds and benches, or move them to higher ground</li>
        <li>Collect together medicines, important documents, mementos, photos and pets and take them with</li>
        <li>Take three days’ supply of clothing, medication and pet needs with you</li>
        <li>Turn off electricity and gas at the mains and lock you doors and windows when you evacuate</li>
        <li>Remaining in your home or business during flooding is dangerous and may put your life at risk</li>
    </ul>
